              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "OLMS",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The Incident Proton Beam (100 MEV, 50 NANOAMP.) Was",
                "Degraded by be-Absorbers. The Used Energy-Range",
                "Relation is not Quoted.",
                "The Fission Product Yields were Measured on-Line with",
                "A Mass Spectrometer, the Mass-Discrimination Efficiency",
                "Of Which was Calibrated with the Isotopes of Natural",
                "Ba and Sn. The Mass-Separated Ions were Counted by",
                "Means of an Electron Multiplier.",
                "The Identification of the Separated in-Isotopes was",
                "Confirmed by Measuring Their Radioactive Decay, That",
                "Of the Ga-Isotopes was Based on the Chemical Similarity",
                "Of Ga and in.",
                "No Information is Given  Whether and How the Proton",
                "Flux was Determined and Accounted For. It was Possibly",
                "Regarded by the Normalization Procedure Applied (SEE",
                "COMMENT UNDER REACTION) And Therefore not Measured",
                " (COMMENT BY THE COMPILER OF KACHAPAG)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural U-Oxide  Deposited in Layers of About 5.4",
                "Mg/Cm**2 on 28.6 Mg/Cm**2 Thick Graphite Disks of 12.7",
                "Mm Diameter. A Total of 23 Disks were Assembled As",
                "Target Within the Oven of the on-Line Mass-Separator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Measured Relative Independent Yields were Corrected",
                "For Diffusion Times in the Target Assembly, Decay of",
                "The Radioactive Isotopes, and the Mass-Discrimination",
                "Of the Separator. No Corrections were Applied For the",
                "Cumulative Yields. Their Contributions were Believed to",
                "Be Small Due to the Fact That Yields were Measured",
                "During and Between Prompt Beam Pulses (PULSE DURATION-",
                "0.2 SEC, PULSE DISTANCE- 2 SEC) And That by",
                "Subtracting the Off-Beam Yield Cumulative Events and",
                "Background Should Mostly be Cancelled. Furthermore, the",
                "Precursors Should have Much Longer Diffusion Times."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Given Errors Represent Only the Relative",
                "Errors Due to Statistics.  Not Included are Errors",
                "Resulting from the Normalization Procedure.",
                "Systematic Errors Due to the Energy Loss of the Protons",
                "In the Target, Especially at Lower Beam Energies,",
                "Resulting in a Widening of the Isotopic Distribution,",
                "Are Also Disregarded."
              ]
            }
          ],
